t with timely expert medical evaluations and treatment, and serves the community as a resource for prevention, research and education. Located at 2300 N. Rockton Ave. in Rockford, this program receives referrals from the Department of Family and Community Services, law enforcement and physicians in northwest Illinois. We accept most insurance and have strong affiliations with our local health care partners: SwedishAmerican: A Division of UW Health, Mercyhealth and OSF Saint Anthony Medical Center.  In addition to our College of Medicine Rockford facilities, many hospitals, clinics, treatment centers, hospices and other health care facilities in the Rockford area serve as teaching sites. Many doctors in the area are on our faculty and train medical students and residents in their practices throughout Rockford and around the state. Patient Forms & Resources Patient Release of Information Form (print and mail or fax to the clinic) Patient Release of Information Form – SPANISH – (print and mail or fax to the clinic) Patient Care UI Health Patient Portal Insurance Coverage Patient Privacy: HIPAA UI Health L.P. Johnson Family Health Center Insurance and Payment Policies Pregnancy Services Your Health Care Team UI Health Thyroid Disease in Pregnancy Clinic Local Affiliations About  Education  Research  Patient Care  Departments  News  Giving INFORMATION FOR: Prospective and Current Students  Faculty & Staff  Alumni & Friends  Patients  Businesses and Community RESOURCES: UIC Directory  Blackboard  Emergency Information  Contact Us  Apply Now  Give  Contact Us Connect with us!    If you have questions, comments, or problems accessing this site, please E-mail the webmaster  © Copyright 2019 University of Illinois College of Medicine   | Privacy Statement College of Medicine | Chicago | Peoria | Rockford | Urbana                                                                                                                                             